{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7716f188-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s225"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"225"},"text":"§ 225.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Laws applicable; easements and rights-of-way","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whenever consistent with the primary purposes of Grand Canyon National Park, the Act of February fifteenth, nineteen hundred and one,","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002038"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002038"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" applicable to the locations of rights of way in certain national parks and the national forests for irrigation and other purposes, and subsequent Acts shall be and remain applicable to the lands included within the park. The Secretary of the Interior may, in his discretion and upon such conditions as he may deem proper, grant easements or rights of way for railroads upon or across the park."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7716f189-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1919-02-26/ch44/s5"},"text":"Feb. 26, 1919, ch. 44, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/1178"},"text":"40 Stat. 1178","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7716f18a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7716f18b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7716f18c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Act of February fifteenth, nineteen hundred and one, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1901-02-15/ch372"},"text":"act Feb. 15, 1901, ch. 372","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/790"},"text":"31 Stat. 790","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s959"},"text":"section 959 of Title 43","children":[],"tail":", Public Lands. The Act, insofar as it related to National Park System units, was repealed and restated as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t54/s100902/a"},"text":"section 100902(a) of Title 54","children":[],"tail":", National Park Service and Related Programs, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3, 7, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3094"},"text":"128 Stat. 3094","children":[],"tail":", 3272."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
